missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:5:The attack is mostly correct. The original chain identifies a genuinely different structural reservoir: exact stochastic transport and martingale formulas for Navier-Stokes are not interchangeable with standard Eulerian energy estimates. That is a real positive. But the attack is right that the chain delays the decisive question for too long: whether one exact stochastic observable yields coercive, localizable, endpoint-relevant control rather than an elegant reformulation.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:34:This is the real bottleneck, and the original chain left too much heavy lifting for it. The attack is also right that a bare martingale bound is not enough unless it controls a named concentration or stretching quantity, and that importing a stronger framework can be parasitic if it merely smuggles back the deterministic hard part.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:19:What is missing is a benchmark set. The chain should force comparison against known geometric regularity mechanisms from Constantin-Fefferman-Majda and the later vorticity-direction coherence literature. Without that, the Tao filter has no calibration.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-02.md:67:The chain says it is meaningfully different because it centers coherent structures and geometry, but that is exactly where there is already a large literature. Without an explicit map against Constantin-Fefferman-Majda, Deng-Hou-Yu, geometric depletion work, and near-Beltrami discussions, "different" is not established. There is a real redundancy risk.
